  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Peel and grate the <strong>parsnip<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p><p>Grate the <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on)</p><p>Peel and finely slice the <strong>brown onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1631108697235-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1631108697235-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1631108697235-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1631108697235-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1631108697235-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>sliced onion</strong>, <strong>grated potato</strong> and <strong>grated</strong> <strong>parsnip </strong>to the middle of a <strong>tea</strong> <strong>towel</strong></p><p>Bring the four corners together to form a ball, twist the ball and squeeze out as much liquid as you can</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1631108701173-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1631108701173-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1631108701173-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1631108701173-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1631108701173-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> onion, potato &</strong> <strong>parsnip mix </strong>to a bowl with a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Add<strong> </strong>3 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[6 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour </strong>and 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil </strong>and<strong> </strong>give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>rösti mix</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1631108705383-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1631108705383-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1631108705383-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1631108705383-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1631108705383-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Line a baking tray with <strong>non-stick baking paper</strong></p><p>Tip: Cooking for 4? Use 2 trays!</p><p>Separate the <strong>rösti mix </strong>into 4 <span class=\"text-danger\">[8]</span> and shape into firm potato cakes</p><p>Add the <strong>potato cakes</strong> to the baking tray<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> with a generous drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and put the tray in the oven for an initial 15 min</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1631108708741-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1631108708741-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1631108708741-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1631108708741-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1631108708741-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the parsnip röstis have cooked for 15 min, flip them over and add the <strong>asparagus </strong>with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Put the tray<span class=\"text-danger\">[s] </span>back in the oven for a final 10 min or until the asparagus is  tender and the parsnip röstis are golden – these are your <strong>parsnip röstis </strong>and <strong>roasted asparagus</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1631108712436-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1631108712436-x400.jpg",
